ENTRY       EC 1.13.11.74               Enzyme
NAME        2-aminophenol 1,6-dioxygenase;
            amnA (gene name);
            amnB (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on single donors with incorporation of molecular oxygen (oxygenases);
            With incorporation of two atoms of oxygen
SYSNAME     2-aminophenol:oxygen 1,6-oxidoreductase (decyclizing)
REACTION    2-aminophenol + O2 = 2-aminomuconate 6-semialdehyde [RN:R05405]
ALL_REAC    R05405
SUBSTRATE   2-aminophenol [CPD:C01987];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     2-aminomuconate 6-semialdehyde [CPD:C03824]
COMMENT     The enzyme, a member of the nonheme-iron(II)-dependent dioxygenase family, is an extradiol-type dioxygenase that utilizes a non-heme ferrous iron to cleave the aromatic ring at the meta position (relative to the hydroxyl substituent). The enzyme also has some activity with 2-amino-5-methylphenol and 2-amino-4-methylphenol [1]. The enzyme from the bacterium Comamonas testosteroni CNB-1 also has the activity of EC 1.3.1.105, 2-amino-5-chlorophenol 1,6-dioxygenase [2].
